{
  "_doc": "Streets of New Capenna (SNC) Draft + Collector recipes. The draft block was generated by scripts/gen-booster-contents.mjs from data/_collation-facts/snc.json (source: The Collation Project, lethe.xyz/mtg/collation) and is kept verbatim \u2014 do not hand-edit it unless you also remove its facts source. Set composition: 101C / 80U / 60R / 20M; four variations of each basic land; 36 packs per box; printed in USA + Belgium (US printing modeled). The collector block was authored by hand from the official Collecting Streets of New Capenna article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-streets-of-new-capenna-2022-04-07) plus the SNC Product Overview. SNC predates Play/Set-Booster consolidation: per assignment we model only Draft + Collector (Set Boosters skipped) and set authoritative:true so only those two types are offered. Sub-set codes: SNC main, NCC New Capenna Commander (extended-art Commander rare/mythic found in Collector Boosters), ASNC art series, TSNC tokens. Collector Booster = 15 cards + 1 foil double-faced token; slot map from the official breakdown: 4 foil commons, 2 foil uncommons, 2 non-foil showcase (golden-age/skyscraper) commons/uncommons, 1 foil showcase common/uncommon OR gilded common/uncommon, 1 foil metropolis full-art basic land (always), 1 foil rare/mythic, 1 non-foil extended-art Commander (NCC) rare/mythic, 1 non-foil extended-art rare/mythic, 1 non-foil Booster Fun (showcase/borderless) rare/mythic, 1 traditional foil Booster Fun rare/mythic (showcase/extended-art/borderless, occasionally foil-etched art-deco or gilded). Per-pack drop rates cited verbatim: 25% of Collector Boosters contain a gilded common/uncommon, 13% contain a gilded rare/mythic; foil-etched versions of all nine art-deco cards are exclusive to Collector Boosters. SNC's 'golden age / skyscraper / art deco' frames are modeled with the showcase filter; foil-etched art-deco uses etched_foil; gilded uses gilded_foil. No serialized cards in this product.",
